03:24.480 --> 03:27.154
REID: A murdered child
on a mortuary slab.

03:27.280 --> 03:30.955
The entropy of the universe,
extended to a maximum, Mr Dove.

03:39.760 --> 03:42.798
JACKSON: Every stroke of this blade
to the boy's body,

03:42.920 --> 03:44.672
I'm imagining it done to you, sir.

03:46.640 --> 03:48.392
I'm hearing your screams.

03:55.560 --> 03:58.473
NATHANIEL: I do not know
how...how long we sailed,

03:58.600 --> 04:01.194
but I do remember the stench, <i>miss.</i>

04:03.800 --> 04:05.518
I remember the fear.

04:05.640 --> 04:07.119
Go on, sir.

04:08.240 --> 04:13.872
I do not know how my brother
found Rabbi Leon.

04:14.000 --> 04:15.320
But he brung him from Paris

04:15.440 --> 04:20.560
in the hope he might know
how best to quiet my tempers.

04:20.680 --> 04:23.718
But that counsel,
he did not soothe me.

04:23.840 --> 04:25.558
It only roused my hunger.

04:25.680 --> 04:28.194
I had to feed it,

04:28.320 --> 04:31.551
cos, you see, miss,
he had shown me myself.

04:31.680 --> 04:33.114
My childhood self.

04:34.280 --> 04:35.759
I saw the forest...

04:37.120 --> 04:38.997
...and the ease and grace with...

04:39.120 --> 04:41.760
with which the wolves
might move through it...

04:44.400 --> 04:46.311
...whilst we simply trudged...

04:48.360 --> 04:51.113
...so heavy and...slow...

04:52.280 --> 04:56.672
...and as the rabbi spoke
of the morning they found her,

04:56.800 --> 04:59.394
I did not think
on the sight of my mother,

04:59.520 --> 05:00.794
no...

05:01.840 --> 05:04.195
...of my mother's body and blood.

05:07.360 --> 05:09.351
I thought only on their...

05:10.920 --> 05:12.274
...power...

05:14.240 --> 05:16.470
...the pure purpose of their need...

05:19.240 --> 05:21.470
...and how that need might be met.

05:23.160 --> 05:26.790
There's no frothing
or waterlogging to the lungs.

05:26.920 --> 05:31.756
There are, however, tiny
haemorrhages to the lining thereof,

05:31.880 --> 05:33.553
the burst capillaries
beneath the eyelids.

05:33.680 --> 05:35.717
The cause of death was suffocation.

05:37.600 --> 05:40.797
There are contusions
about the neck and face.

05:40.920 --> 05:43.719
Similarly to his fists.

05:43.840 --> 05:47.071
We may therefore presume
his death a violent one.

05:51.120 --> 05:53.509
Within the lining
of the respiratory tract,

05:53.640 --> 05:57.554
there are trace elements inhaled at
the point of death and adhered within.

05:57.680 --> 05:59.432
So, we have a wool fibre.

05:59.560 --> 06:04.111
The wool is an alpaca blend,
charcoal-grey in colour,

06:04.240 --> 06:06.629
most likely from the person
who throttled him.

06:06.760 --> 06:09.798
The suspect is frequently seen
sporting such an overcoat, Inspector.

06:09.920 --> 06:12.070
- Correct?
- DOVE: Grey alpaca.

06:12.200 --> 06:16.239
Am I the only man in London
with a woollen coat? No, I am not.

06:16.360 --> 06:19.193
You have no witness,
no physical evidence.

06:19.320 --> 06:21.789
You have no fingerprints, Mr Reid.

06:24.800 --> 06:27.155
You must surely see it, Drummond.

06:27.280 --> 06:29.476
These men,
these criminal murdering men,

06:29.600 --> 06:32.911
wish to tar me with the black pitch
of their own hearts.

06:34.000 --> 06:35.752
DRUMMOND: Mr Reid.

06:35.880 --> 06:38.269
Captain, please.

06:40.080 --> 06:44.074
The boy must be found on the man
or the man on the boy.

06:49.040 --> 06:53.034
Augustus and Abel, they...
they found a man...

06:54.080 --> 06:56.469
...a madman,
known to the police as such,

06:56.600 --> 06:59.353
for his attack on...
on another rabbi, see.

06:59.480 --> 07:02.677
And, sir, that was Mr Isaac Bloom?

07:02.800 --> 07:04.154
Yes,

07:04.280 --> 07:08.638
and I heard them say how
they would take my acts...

07:11.400 --> 07:12.959
...and they would hand them to him.

07:13.080 --> 07:15.594
DRUMMOND: Captain, whatever it is
you hunt for, please find it.

07:15.720 --> 07:18.314
DOVE: He will find nothing,
because there is nothing to find,

07:18.440 --> 07:21.671
save the wreckage of your life
along with theirs.

07:30.600 --> 07:31.795
My, sir. You are flush.

07:36.600 --> 07:37.635
Mimi.

07:40.200 --> 07:44.080
- JACKSON: Are you feeling all right?
- Other than flu, I'm fine.

07:50.760 --> 07:52.080
Are you feeling quite well, sir?

07:52.200 --> 07:53.679
(GRUNTS)

08:00.600 --> 08:03.399
There's infection within.

08:03.520 --> 08:05.557
A swollen tongue.

08:06.520 --> 08:10.957
The throat red with infection,
an infection he might have set loose

08:11.080 --> 08:13.230
on any soul with whom
he came into contact,

08:13.360 --> 08:16.637
particularly one which
was trying to kill him...

08:19.040 --> 08:20.917
...because he would have fought.

08:22.880 --> 08:24.871
He would have spat and screamed,

08:25.000 --> 08:28.277
he would have clutched and clawed
for the breathing of air,

08:28.400 --> 08:31.438
and he would have sprayed
that infection all over the man

08:31.560 --> 08:35.235
whose arms were now choking
the ten little years of life from him.

08:39.600 --> 08:41.352
Does a fever rise in you, sir?

08:41.480 --> 08:44.916
Is there a chill through your bones
like a nameless haunting?

08:45.960 --> 08:48.713
Well, I have the name for it.

08:50.120 --> 08:52.396
Oh, you brave, clever little boy,
Robin Sumner,

08:52.520 --> 08:54.830
the gift you bring with you.

09:03.400 --> 09:05.994
And, sir, will you confirm
your spoken confession

09:06.120 --> 09:07.997
that you murdered
Inspector Bennet Drake?

09:09.880 --> 09:10.870
Yes, miss.

09:12.480 --> 09:16.394
And Assistant Commissioner Dove
had full knowledge of this?

09:17.440 --> 09:19.397
Augustus knew it.

09:22.440 --> 09:25.080
Augustus knew it all.

09:25.200 --> 09:29.159
And, um...how was it
Augustus killed Abel?

09:29.280 --> 09:31.032
(SIGHS)

09:31.160 --> 09:34.391
Abel Croker wished to take my life...

09:36.120 --> 09:37.713
...but Augustus Dove, he...

09:40.320 --> 09:41.640
...he took his instead.

09:45.240 --> 09:47.072
Gustus saved me.

09:48.440 --> 09:49.510
Gustus...

09:51.280 --> 09:53.351
...always saved me.

09:59.880 --> 10:02.156
Reid, did you catch
scarlet fever as a boy?

10:02.280 --> 10:04.874
- I did.
- So did I. Caitlin too.

10:05.000 --> 10:09.119
Now, what that means is that, once
caught, we cannot catch it again.

10:09.240 --> 10:11.550
Now, Miss Morton, I believe,
has not suffered it before,

10:11.680 --> 10:13.079
because she suffers it now.

10:13.200 --> 10:15.919
And where else
might she have contracted it,

10:16.040 --> 10:19.590
but from a sickly child
who's taking refuge with her?

10:23.840 --> 10:27.435
It's like a string of purple pearls.

10:27.560 --> 10:29.790
Streptococcus pyogenes.

10:38.240 --> 10:40.197
It's scarlet fever.

11:46.560 --> 11:48.073
(IN HALES)

11:48.200 --> 11:50.077
(DOOR OPENS)

11:50.200 --> 11:51.952
Sir? Commissioner Bradford.

12:12.240 --> 12:13.833
Well, Fred. What do you say?

12:15.040 --> 12:18.158
It is a cat-meat soup, Teddy.

12:18.280 --> 12:20.954
You should know
your own presence here,

12:21.080 --> 12:24.914
a retired civilian gone rogue,
it's unconscionable.

12:25.040 --> 12:27.919
But, under current circumstances,

12:28.040 --> 12:32.034
there is one more intervention
you might perform for us.

12:33.960 --> 12:35.109
Reid.

12:37.040 --> 12:38.997
There will be an inquiry, internal,

12:39.120 --> 12:42.875
but we here have decided
what Edmund Reid's fate shall be.

12:44.000 --> 12:47.470
ABBERLINE: And the others?
Your man Dove?

12:47.600 --> 12:51.992
BRADFORD: Imagine the world's joy
at our disgrace, Fred. No.

12:52.120 --> 12:53.918
Sudden illness.

12:54.040 --> 12:56.316
Lengthy convalescence.

12:56.440 --> 12:58.272
Disappearance from public life.

12:58.400 --> 13:00.357
Get him out.

13:00.480 --> 13:04.189
BRADFORD: Dartmoor Prison
will receive a new inmate, however.

13:05.560 --> 13:08.029
The victim of a clerical blunder.

13:08.160 --> 13:10.276
His paperwork lost.

13:10.400 --> 13:12.710
The man likewise.

13:16.680 --> 13:18.478
Gustus?

13:29.800 --> 13:32.189
Think how far we came, brother.

13:32.320 --> 13:34.118
How very far.

13:35.520 --> 13:37.750
Gustus, where...where do you go?

13:37.880 --> 13:40.315
Hush. We must be brave.

13:57.760 --> 14:00.593
I knew chaos and horror
a good long time

14:00.720 --> 14:02.757
before I came to Whitechapel, Mr Reid.

14:16.560 --> 14:18.437
I'm to bring you out as well, sir.

14:25.320 --> 14:27.596
Mr Abberline's
waiting for you outside.

14:30.920 --> 14:34.834
Augustus Dove is to be
buried deep and forgot.

14:34.960 --> 14:37.190
Our shame alongside.

14:37.320 --> 14:40.950
Is this the reason for our stroll?
How else is the pit to be limed, Fred?

14:41.080 --> 14:45.597
The brother, that beast,
he is to be choked and in short order.

14:45.720 --> 14:47.711
The woman Hart similarly.

14:52.320 --> 14:55.073
What else, Edmund? Clemency?

14:57.960 --> 15:00.952
- And the Captain?
- Send him home.

15:01.080 --> 15:02.718
Where he belongs. Besides...

15:02.840 --> 15:08.358
it is not the fate of that evil pair
brings me to you now, but your own.

15:08.480 --> 15:11.074
And that too is decided, I imagine?

15:12.080 --> 15:13.593
A little further yet.

15:22.120 --> 15:23.599
That is right, my friend.

15:25.400 --> 15:27.437
Think of what you and I once found
in a tenement room

15:27.560 --> 15:29.551
off that courtyard beyond.

15:30.600 --> 15:34.275
The cut and strewn remains
of the Ripper's last victim.

15:35.520 --> 15:37.238
Ten years ago, Edmund.

15:37.360 --> 15:39.397
Ten years.

15:39.520 --> 15:44.549
That barbarism then, that which these
Dove brothers have only now enacted.

15:46.480 --> 15:48.835
They were forged
from the same furnace,

15:48.960 --> 15:53.670
a furnace which requires
permanent vigilance, Edmund.

15:53.800 --> 15:57.111
A watchman...set for the night,

15:57.240 --> 16:00.358
when that fire finds
another crack in the world

16:00.480 --> 16:03.359
and sets its creatures free
once more.

16:11.040 --> 16:13.270
Bennet Drake was a fine man.

16:13.400 --> 16:14.720
But he...

16:16.320 --> 16:18.357
That paleface Drummond,

16:18.480 --> 16:21.233
they do not see.

16:22.240 --> 16:24.629
Not in the way you see.

16:24.760 --> 16:26.751
You are needed here, Mr Reid.

16:28.160 --> 16:29.480
My crimes?

16:31.160 --> 16:32.992
Wish to face them, do you?

16:33.120 --> 16:34.793
They are true. I would own them.

16:34.920 --> 16:40.313
I am to tell you that such an owning
will not find favour...

16:41.880 --> 16:47.000
...and to extend Commissioner
Bradford's wish and invitation

16:47.120 --> 16:52.320
for Edmund Reid to resume
his command at Leman Street.

16:57.640 --> 17:00.109
That is some bold denial to mount.

17:01.160 --> 17:04.949
It is a public redemption
of a good man wronged.

17:05.079 --> 17:06.400
And if I refuse?

17:08.720 --> 17:12.679
Well, then, your American will not
find himself so easily forgot.

17:12.800 --> 17:16.839
In point of fact,
his many misdemeanours will be

17:16.960 --> 17:19.759
pursued with full rigour...

17:21.040 --> 17:24.112
...and he will dangle, Edmund.

17:27.280 --> 17:28.998
(LOCK CLICKS)

17:30.240 --> 17:32.880
- Have the man brought out in irons.
- Miss Susan?

17:37.200 --> 17:39.510
Where do they take me?

17:39.640 --> 17:41.790
Wait. Wait. Please.
Please, please. Please, wait.

17:41.920 --> 17:44.958
No! Don't! Stop!
Don't! Stop! Leave him!

17:45.080 --> 17:47.196
No, please! Where do you take him?

17:59.080 --> 18:02.277
JACKSON: I'm with you, darling.
I'm coming too.

18:04.440 --> 18:06.556
Come with me, Miss Hart.

18:08.080 --> 18:10.833
Wait, Drummond.
What...what about me?

18:10.960 --> 18:13.873
What about me, God damn it?
What...what about me? Take me.

18:14.000 --> 18:16.116
Your prisoner, Mr Reid.

18:18.200 --> 18:20.032
Reid? What the hell?

18:20.160 --> 18:21.992
Where's he taking her?

18:30.920 --> 18:32.877
Reid?

18:34.760 --> 18:36.114
Reid?

18:42.760 --> 18:45.639
Reid. God damn it. What?

18:45.760 --> 18:48.149
Your personal effects,
Captain Jackson.

18:52.800 --> 18:54.552
You're releasing me?

18:57.800 --> 19:00.394
- MAN: Murderer!
- WOMAN: Hang till you die!

19:00.520 --> 19:02.796
(SHOUTING OUTSIDE)

19:02.920 --> 19:05.434
Caitlin! Caitlin.

19:07.320 --> 19:09.038
You sons of bitches!

19:09.160 --> 19:10.833
- Let him go.
- Let me go!

19:10.960 --> 19:12.758
- Let me go!
- Let him go.

19:12.880 --> 19:14.712
God damn it!

19:14.840 --> 19:16.513
For him?

19:18.480 --> 19:20.835
You did this for him?

19:20.960 --> 19:23.952
I did it before.
I'll do it again. I'll save you.

19:24.080 --> 19:27.072
No. No, you will not.

19:28.280 --> 19:30.317
You are a father now.

19:30.440 --> 19:32.511
What kind of example
would that be for our son?

19:32.640 --> 19:33.550
No.

19:33.680 --> 19:35.876
What kind would I be,
if I let you die?

19:36.000 --> 19:38.389
But you must, you see.

19:39.640 --> 19:42.519
Because he must have
one of us to care for him...

19:44.280 --> 19:46.510
...and it seems that one will be you.

19:47.760 --> 19:49.592
It was you and me.

19:53.400 --> 19:55.277
You and me.

19:55.400 --> 19:57.630
And it ever will be.

19:57.760 --> 19:59.956
Because of our boy.

20:00.080 --> 20:02.117
We are in him.

20:02.240 --> 20:03.435
One.

20:05.040 --> 20:08.032
So, you go and you raise him good.

20:08.160 --> 20:09.355
Raise him right.

20:10.760 --> 20:13.070
I'll think of how we were made

20:13.200 --> 20:15.237
and I'll do the reverse.

20:28.120 --> 20:30.430
I love you.

20:32.200 --> 20:34.032
I will never stop.

20:40.120 --> 20:41.997
Please, Mr Drummond,

20:42.120 --> 20:43.713
take me away.

21:30.040 --> 21:31.110
Bye.

21:31.240 --> 21:32.958
You little yahoo.

21:37.280 --> 21:40.272
Come on, Connor,
just leave her be now.

21:42.240 --> 21:44.436
Mimi, I...

21:44.560 --> 21:45.880
No.

21:46.000 --> 21:47.593
Please.

22:04.600 --> 22:05.635
Walk with you?

22:05.760 --> 22:08.513
Is there a law that says you can't?

22:09.600 --> 22:10.999
Well, then.

22:20.080 --> 22:22.230
(SHIP'S HORN BLARES)

22:23.760 --> 22:25.433
Well, goodbye, Master Judge.

22:27.680 --> 22:29.034
Shake the man's hand, Connor.

22:40.560 --> 22:42.039
I'll be seeing you, Reid.

22:43.080 --> 22:44.434
Captain.

22:46.440 --> 22:47.430
Are you going there now?

22:47.560 --> 22:49.517
I am.

22:50.600 --> 22:52.352
Erm...

22:52.480 --> 22:53.993
Tell her, erm...

22:54.120 --> 22:55.394
Tell her...

22:55.520 --> 22:56.794
What?

23:01.640 --> 23:03.199
Ah, never mind.

23:06.040 --> 23:07.360
It don't matter.

23:30.800 --> 23:33.110
(SHIP'S HORN BLARES)

24:23.120 --> 24:24.315
Nathaniel.

24:24.440 --> 24:25.589
Miss Susan.

24:25.720 --> 24:28.997
Mr Theakston, please,
only for a moment.

24:30.320 --> 24:32.357
Do not let them touch.

24:41.000 --> 24:43.355
We are to go together, then.

24:43.480 --> 24:45.869
- One after the other.
- Mm-hm.

24:48.120 --> 24:50.270
They've found a priest
who speaks my mother's tongue.

24:50.400 --> 24:55.349
He says if...if I am repenting,
I should be spared hell.

24:57.000 --> 25:00.118
But why should I be spared it
just for the saying of some words?

25:00.240 --> 25:02.550
But you feel the regret?

25:06.840 --> 25:08.114
Nothing but.

25:08.240 --> 25:11.915
Miss Susan,
they must be allowed to proceed.

25:13.240 --> 25:15.880
Perhaps I shall speak
with this priest after all.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.150
Forgive her, I shall say...

25:19.200 --> 25:20.918
...and let her see
her Connor once more.

25:24.240 --> 25:25.310
I should be grateful.

25:27.240 --> 25:30.198
I'm...I'm...I'm coming after you,
Nathaniel.

25:30.320 --> 25:32.834
I shall be following you on,
calling your name,

25:32.960 --> 25:36.112
and, whatever it is that waits,
we will go there together.

26:34.960 --> 26:37.315
(m LATIN)

26:50.200 --> 26:52.271
(LOCK RATTLES)

28:20.480 --> 28:21.959
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

28:22.080 --> 28:24.959
DRAKE: Mr Reid! Mr Reid, sir!

28:25.080 --> 28:27.674
- (KNOCKS)
- Please, sir, raise yourself!

28:27.800 --> 28:30.997
Stop your hammering, Sergeant.
I'm here.

28:31.120 --> 28:34.476
Mr Reid, you must come, sir.
There is another.

28:48.440 --> 28:50.511
(RETCHING)

28:56.880 --> 28:59.952
Her name was Mary Jane Kelly.

29:03.600 --> 29:05.671
Edmund.

29:05.800 --> 29:07.438
I want to unmake the world.

30:14.800 --> 30:17.269
- (PIANO PLAYS)
- (CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

30:21.440 --> 30:22.635
Drum!

30:24.200 --> 30:26.953
Drum! The toasts.

30:29.720 --> 30:31.631
(GLASS TINKLES)

30:31.760 --> 30:33.114
(CHATTER STOPS)

30:38.400 --> 30:39.390
My Mathilda.

30:42.560 --> 30:45.120
- This is the last, I believe.
- Oh, thank you, sir.

30:45.240 --> 30:47.959
There's no need to "sir" me,
not any longer.

30:51.520 --> 30:54.239
So, you really couldn't have
waited another few weeks?

30:54.360 --> 30:56.749
Samuel doesn't want the child
born here, Father.

30:56.880 --> 30:58.279
Of course.

30:58.400 --> 31:01.358
- Well, travel carefully.
- Father, please.

31:01.480 --> 31:04.632
It is the Great Western to Cheltenham
Spa, not a steam turbine to the Congo.

31:04.760 --> 31:06.558
I know, Mathilda, but, erm...

31:06.680 --> 31:07.875
Bad things happen everywhere. I know.

31:08.000 --> 31:10.310
You are my daughter, and I worry.

31:10.440 --> 31:11.430
Don't.

31:15.240 --> 31:18.437
Remember the conviction
that you held that I was alive?

31:19.520 --> 31:20.794
Yes, of course.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.593
Then surely it is not such a struggle

31:22.720 --> 31:25.838
to hold the simpler belief
that I am well?

31:36.160 --> 31:37.070
Mr Reid.

31:37.200 --> 31:38.190
Samuel.

31:40.160 --> 31:41.150
Right.

31:45.320 --> 31:47.231
- You will visit, of course?
- No, Drum.

31:47.360 --> 31:50.352
He won't come. He won't ever.

31:52.040 --> 31:53.439
He cannot.

32:26.280 --> 32:29.033
- Sergeant.
- Sir.

32:29.160 --> 32:32.516
- He is within?
- He is, Mr Abberline.

32:42.440 --> 32:43.760
Nothing?

32:43.880 --> 32:45.393
A witness.

32:45.520 --> 32:46.874
Of sorts.

32:47.000 --> 32:47.990
Description?

32:48.120 --> 32:50.031
Five foot six inches,

32:50.160 --> 32:53.312
fair, curled moustache, 34 years of age...

32:55.320 --> 32:56.310
."about

32:57.600 --> 32:59.193
Well, I shall add it to the catalogue.

33:00.880 --> 33:02.553
These are not clues, Fred.

33:02.680 --> 33:06.116
They are half-glimpsed imaginings,
a tangle of shadows,

33:06.240 --> 33:07.913
and you and I floundering at them,

33:08.040 --> 33:11.795
in the ever-vainer hope that
we might corral them into meaning,

33:11.920 --> 33:13.593
when we will not.

33:13.720 --> 33:15.074
We will not.

33:25.080 --> 33:26.400
I said.

33:27.760 --> 33:30.400
I almost begged it of you
when you lost her.

33:34.560 --> 33:35.470
Forgive me.

33:35.600 --> 33:38.911
When your Mathilda
went down on that boat.

33:40.600 --> 33:42.477
But I say it again.

33:42.600 --> 33:45.160
Tend to your wife. Take the leave.

33:45.280 --> 33:47.794
- You are clue it.
- I prefer to work.

33:47.920 --> 33:49.991
Then work, Edmund!

33:50.120 --> 33:51.679
Fight!

34:02.320 --> 34:04.675
No, Mr Reid. Go home.

34:15.040 --> 34:17.998
- Here, Mr Reid, let us get you home.
- No, no.

34:18.120 --> 34:20.350
Sergeant, Sergeant, Sergeant.
Sergeant.

34:20.480 --> 34:22.232
My girl is gone.

34:22.360 --> 34:23.793
My wife will barely
look me in the eye,

34:23.920 --> 34:26.036
without the wish to spit in it
and curse me for the loss of her.

34:26.159 --> 34:28.275
So...no home.

34:32.040 --> 34:34.156
- Come, sir, please.
- No! Damn you!

34:34.280 --> 34:37.351
Damn your care!
Damn your endless fawning!

34:37.480 --> 34:39.232
Are you a dog?

34:39.360 --> 34:40.475
Are you?

34:40.600 --> 34:43.399
- I am not, Inspector.
- Then stop following me!

34:45.880 --> 34:47.791
It shan't bring you any good.

35:09.400 --> 35:14.395
That's it, up a bit. More, more,
more to me. How's that, sir?

35:14.520 --> 35:16.272
Afternoon, Inspector.

35:20.040 --> 35:21.713
Six months they're gone.

35:22.800 --> 35:25.838
He is now a teacher. She, erm...

35:25.960 --> 35:27.792
She writes a novel, she says,

35:27.920 --> 35:29.479
and the child prospers.

35:29.600 --> 35:31.557
Have you been to see her, the child?

35:31.680 --> 35:32.750
Er...no. Not yet, no.

35:32.880 --> 35:35.190
Your granddaughter, Edmund.

35:35.320 --> 35:36.913
Soon, however.

35:37.040 --> 35:39.634
I shall, erm, take some holiday.

35:45.920 --> 35:47.752
And so, your visit?

35:52.760 --> 35:56.276
This is the death certificate
of a woman named Mary Spinks.

35:56.400 --> 35:59.552
Her named husband, see,
is George Chapman,

35:59.680 --> 36:01.353
only that is not his true name.

36:02.480 --> 36:04.357
Sorry, Fred, but...

36:04.480 --> 36:08.633
George Chapman only became so in 1895.

36:08.760 --> 36:11.639
Before that, however, he was called...

36:11.760 --> 36:14.354
Severin Klosowski.

36:15.520 --> 36:19.400
The Severin Klosowski who was once a
suspect of ours in the Ripper murders?

36:19.520 --> 36:22.194
But he has gone to America.

36:22.320 --> 36:24.960
Not since 1892, he has not.

36:25.080 --> 36:27.037
He has returned to this country.

36:28.360 --> 36:31.751
Ah. Confidential autopsy report.

36:33.480 --> 36:35.118
His wife.

36:35.240 --> 36:36.878
He beat her.

36:37.000 --> 36:39.674
Ceaselessly. You know?

36:39.800 --> 36:42.792
- He's a brute, I'm sure.
- And more than that.

36:42.920 --> 36:45.036
Severin Klosowski.

36:45.160 --> 36:50.360
1885, he finishes his surgical studies
at the Praga Hospital in Warsaw.

36:50.480 --> 36:53.040
June '87, he's in London as a barber,

36:53.160 --> 36:54.878
a position in a shop

36:55.000 --> 36:58.755
on the corner of Whitechapel
High Street and George Yard...

36:58.880 --> 37:01.554
Yes, the skills and the knives,
Fred. I do not forget.

37:01.680 --> 37:05.639
George Yard, where Martha Tabram
was killed in August '88.

37:05.760 --> 37:07.797
I never credited Miss Tabram as his.

37:07.920 --> 37:09.593
Oh, did you not?

37:09.720 --> 37:12.712
And the world must kowtow to
Ed Reid's theories, must it?

37:12.840 --> 37:14.274
Not mine, no.

37:14.400 --> 37:15.993
Her killer was right-handed.
The Ripper used his left.

37:16.120 --> 37:18.714
You know that, Fred, you know that,
and you sit here now

37:18.840 --> 37:22.196
in the belief I might recommence
those same investigations.

37:22.320 --> 37:25.836
- The file remains open, Inspector.
- And what?!

37:25.960 --> 37:28.998
A man we once identified as a suspect
has a wife who dies of consumption,

37:29.120 --> 37:32.078
and you are roused
from your retirement to berate me

37:32.200 --> 37:35.272
that I do not set myself
and my station house to his capture?

37:35.400 --> 37:38.313
Read the autopsy, Inspector!

37:38.440 --> 37:42.149
Consumption would present itself as
a hardening rash on the arms and legs.

37:42.280 --> 37:45.750
What she had were pustular swellings
around the eyes and mouth.

37:45.880 --> 37:48.679
Now, I am not your American surgeon,

37:48.800 --> 37:50.916
but I know the symptoms
of antimony poisoning.

37:51.040 --> 37:51.996
Fred! Fred.

37:52.120 --> 37:56.398
Even if it were true and proved,
it is still only a poisoning.

37:56.520 --> 37:59.353
The man that we hunted
eviscerated his victims.

37:59.480 --> 38:02.438
He ripped the flesh
and the organs from their bodies.

38:02.560 --> 38:08.431
Nevertheless, it is murder by a man
we know capable of that evisceration,

38:08.560 --> 38:10.198
who was proximate to the acts,

38:10.320 --> 38:12.755
who even now is abroad in this town,

38:12.880 --> 38:16.157
acting out his hatred of women
upon their bodies.

38:16.280 --> 38:17.953
Means. Opportunity.

38:18.080 --> 38:19.070
Motive.

38:21.080 --> 38:23.196
Will you bring him in?

38:25.640 --> 38:26.755
No, I will not.

38:26.880 --> 38:29.394
For why?

38:29.520 --> 38:31.670
Because it is a fancy.

38:31.800 --> 38:36.033
It's a dark daydream in the mind
of a retired police officer,

38:36.160 --> 38:39.551
who would do better to return
to his roses and his wife.

38:39.680 --> 38:41.398
It is a case, Edmund.

38:41.520 --> 38:43.750
No, it is a ghost...

38:46.320 --> 38:47.833
...and a dead one at that.

38:53.240 --> 38:55.311
(BREATHES HARD)

38:55.440 --> 38:57.750
Do not think
you've heard the last of this.

39:02.560 --> 39:05.279
Out of my way, you men! Move!

39:05.400 --> 39:07.152
(GASPS)

39:40.320 --> 39:42.709
(LETTERBOX CLICKS)

40:18.200 --> 40:20.157
(CHATTER)

40:31.760 --> 40:33.478
Good evening, Inspector.

40:33.600 --> 40:35.557
And a very good evening to you,
Miss Mimi.

40:37.160 --> 40:39.800
- Ah!
- The dramatic life, Mr Reid.

40:41.360 --> 40:43.636
Ah, it's... it's wonderful.

40:43.760 --> 40:44.795
Remarkable.

40:44.920 --> 40:48.834
Although it is not quite the place
you once knew as home.

40:56.760 --> 40:58.194
(CHEERING)

40:58.320 --> 41:00.072
(APPLAUSE)

41:09.640 --> 41:12.075
MIMI: My friends, my friends.

41:13.120 --> 41:16.272
If I could only tell you
what stories...

41:16.760 --> 41:18.353
(SHOUTING)

41:44.400 --> 41:46.311
Mr Reid, sir.

41:47.360 --> 41:48.634
Mr Reid.

41:50.080 --> 41:51.195
Mr Reid, sir.

41:53.440 --> 41:54.350
Bennet?

41:54.480 --> 41:56.835
Come, let's get you out of here.

41:56.960 --> 41:58.234
How did you find me?

41:58.360 --> 42:00.033
I followed you, didn't I?

42:00.160 --> 42:02.276
Come on, sir.

42:08.320 --> 42:10.277
JACKSON: Hey, slob!

42:11.400 --> 42:13.596
Are you gonna pay for that?

42:15.040 --> 42:17.350
Oh, that's right, Gladys.
Come on, take another step.

42:19.520 --> 42:22.558
Jesus. You ain't winning any beauty
pageants any time soon, are you?

42:25.720 --> 42:26.790
Americans.

42:26.920 --> 42:29.355
All bull, no dog.

42:34.680 --> 42:36.478
I had 'em right where I wanted 'em.

42:50.120 --> 42:51.952
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

43:12.800 --> 43:17.476
Sir. I write as regards my execution of
the will of the late Matthew judge,

43:17.600 --> 43:20.797
in which you are mentioned
as beneficiary.

43:20.920 --> 43:24.356
His assets were limited, but the
enclosed was to be forwarded to you

43:24.480 --> 43:27.632
at the police station
in Whitechapel, London.

43:27.760 --> 43:30.115
It may be of some comfort
for you to know that,

43:30.240 --> 43:33.039
whatever the circumstances
of Mr Judge's past,

43:33.160 --> 43:36.915
his son Connor Judge has now become
the ward of this office here.

43:37.040 --> 43:39.953
We are also the executors,
under grant of probate,

43:40.080 --> 43:43.710
which has recently seen
Master Judge named sole heir

43:43.840 --> 43:45.478
to those assets held by us

43:45.600 --> 43:48.797
of his grandfather,
Mr Theodore Patrick Swift.

44:07.080 --> 44:11.039
REID: He and the boy had been
fishing and were on their way home,

44:11.160 --> 44:13.800
when the girls' mother
came calling for help.

44:13.920 --> 44:18.153
Her two daughters dragged
into the current and downstream.

44:18.280 --> 44:20.590
The Captain swam out,

44:20.720 --> 44:24.270
brought one child to shore
before returning to the other.

44:24.400 --> 44:26.676
She too was saved.

44:29.560 --> 44:31.870
But in so doing,

44:32.000 --> 44:36.198
the cold, so they say, the river
icy with the new spring's thaw...

44:37.880 --> 44:39.632
...his heart gave up.

44:39.760 --> 44:41.956
(SOBS)

44:59.280 --> 45:00.315
Thank you.

45:22.520 --> 45:24.397
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

46:26.840 --> 46:28.194
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

46:31.000 --> 46:32.195
Help you?

46:32.320 --> 46:33.640
Pale ale.

46:37.200 --> 46:39.032
Do you know an Elizabeth Taylor?

46:40.720 --> 46:41.710
Who asks?

46:41.840 --> 46:42.830
Police.

46:45.240 --> 46:46.992
H Division.

46:52.840 --> 46:54.877
(RETCHES)

46:59.040 --> 47:00.951
How long before it begins?

47:01.080 --> 47:03.230
- The inquest?
- Yes.

47:03.360 --> 47:04.759
Two hours, sir.

47:04.880 --> 47:07.190
(GRUNTS)

47:26.160 --> 47:28.834
- Good day to you, Mr Reid.
- (GAVEL BANGS)

47:28.960 --> 47:32.510
OFFICIAL: The Coroner's enquiry
into the death of Mary Jane Kelly

47:32.640 --> 47:34.711
will now come to order.

47:39.880 --> 47:42.998
I live at number 5, Miller's Court.

47:43.120 --> 47:46.078
It's the last house
on the left-hand side of the court.

47:46.200 --> 47:50.034
I'm a widow,
and I get my living on the streets.

47:51.440 --> 47:58.551
# Scenes of my childhood
arise before my gaze

47:58.680 --> 48:03.914
# Bringing recollection
of bygone happy days

48:08.400 --> 48:13.156
# While life does remain
in memoriam, I'll retain... #

48:13.280 --> 48:14.395
(SOBS)

48:14.520 --> 48:20.038
# ...This small violet I plucked
from Mother's grave. #

48:22.520 --> 48:25.911
- Mr Reid?
- What am Ito say to them, Bennet?

48:26.040 --> 48:27.872
Say?

48:28.000 --> 48:30.992
I am expected to stand there
and explain a thing,

48:31.120 --> 48:33.475
and yet I cannot find the explanation.

48:33.600 --> 48:36.353
Because this man's acts
are beyond such?

48:37.560 --> 48:41.030
Sir, I do not say
they are not dreadful.

48:41.160 --> 48:43.197
They are that and more besides.

48:43.320 --> 48:45.311
But, yourself, Mr Abberline,

48:45.440 --> 48:50.116
these newspapermen and councillors
screaming their horror to the skies,

48:50.240 --> 48:54.632
it is as though they imagine some
fantastical creature about his work.

48:56.640 --> 48:58.870
My feeling, Mr Reid,
if you will allow it?

48:59.000 --> 49:01.071
You speak, Bennet.

49:01.200 --> 49:04.192
This here, Miss Kelly,
what was done to her.

49:04.320 --> 49:06.630
It is down to you to name it

49:06.760 --> 49:11.436
so this killer's acts are not
dreamt of as the stuff of fancy,

49:11.560 --> 49:13.153
but known

49:13.280 --> 49:15.669
as the cruelty of men.

49:17.920 --> 49:19.115
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

49:20.320 --> 49:22.516
Hm. That is you, sir.

49:30.920 --> 49:34.117
The whole of the surface of the
abdomen and thighs was removed

49:34.240 --> 49:36.834
and the abdominal cavity
emptied of its viscera.

49:36.960 --> 49:39.236
(PEOPLE MURMUR)

49:39.360 --> 49:42.352
This was found in various parts.

49:43.680 --> 49:46.433
The uterus and kidneys
under the head...

49:49.360 --> 49:51.112
...the liver between the feet,

49:51.240 --> 49:53.470
the intestines by the right side,

49:53.600 --> 49:57.116
and the spleen
by the left side of the body.

50:03.560 --> 50:07.474
The pericardium was open below
and the heart was absent.

50:07.600 --> 50:09.910
(PEOPLE GASP AND MURMUR)

50:10.040 --> 50:12.839
It is concluded
that the mutilation was inflicted

50:12.960 --> 50:15.713
by a person favouring
their left hand.

50:15.840 --> 50:18.912
The bed clothing at the right corner
was saturated with blood

50:19.040 --> 50:21.031
and on the floor beneath was
another pool of blood covering...

50:21.160 --> 50:23.151
Police.

50:23.280 --> 50:25.271
H Division.

50:30.760 --> 50:32.239
My wife is unwell.

50:32.360 --> 50:35.398
Has asked not to be disturbed.

50:37.400 --> 50:40.597
Are you much troubled in this house,
Mr Chapman?

50:43.160 --> 50:47.119
We none of us can be too careful,
Inspector Reid.

50:47.240 --> 50:49.959
What did you say
you wished to ask her?

50:50.080 --> 50:51.479
I hadn't yet.

50:58.000 --> 51:00.640
Well caught. Right hand.

51:01.680 --> 51:03.159
Lost property.

51:03.280 --> 51:06.193
Umbrella. She registered it with us.

51:07.280 --> 51:08.270
And?

51:09.960 --> 51:12.031
I'm sad to say it hasn't been found.

51:12.160 --> 51:14.231
You'll pass the message on, I'm sure.

51:31.480 --> 51:34.074
NEWSPAPER BOY:
Get your final edition here!

51:34.200 --> 51:36.237
Last day of the century!

51:44.120 --> 51:45.952
I left word.

51:46.080 --> 51:48.310
I was unsure whether we...

51:48.440 --> 51:50.113
Well, it is a special occasion

51:50.240 --> 51:52.072
and I wanted to ask if,
after the performances,

51:52.200 --> 51:54.271
we might dine together perhaps?
Er...see in the New Year?

51:54.400 --> 51:55.470
Mr Reid, stop.

51:55.600 --> 51:57.637
I shan't be here tonight.

51:57.760 --> 52:00.957
I have to go to a ball in Richmond.

52:01.080 --> 52:03.674
There is a man who wishes to marry me.

52:03.800 --> 52:05.916
It's his ball.

52:06.040 --> 52:08.395
He's quite old, and, um...

52:10.280 --> 52:13.716
...I am minded to
encourage his attentions,

52:13.840 --> 52:16.480
because I'm frightened

52:16.600 --> 52:19.672
that if I'm still in Whitechapel
at midnight,

52:19.800 --> 52:22.997
I will be here
for another 100 years...

52:24.280 --> 52:26.351
...and though I'm very fond of you,

52:26.480 --> 52:28.835
dear, dear Edmund...

52:29.880 --> 52:32.793
...I'd forever be seeing
the Captain's smile,

52:32.920 --> 52:35.514
smelling his disgusting
whisky breath,

52:35.640 --> 52:37.392
and I refuse

52:37.520 --> 52:39.830
to be haunted by him.

52:41.360 --> 52:42.350
Do you see?

52:48.920 --> 52:50.672
There shall be no-one left but myself.

52:52.320 --> 52:54.277
I think perhaps...

52:55.280 --> 52:57.476
...that is your gift to us.

52:59.760 --> 53:01.512
It's very noble of you.

53:53.160 --> 53:55.834
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

53:58.000 --> 53:59.957
(WHISTLING)

54:19.840 --> 54:26.189
# Scenes of my childhood
arise before my gaze

54:26.320 --> 54:32.919
# Bringing recollections
of bygone happy days

54:33.040 --> 54:35.509
- # When down in the meadow...
- # When down in the meadow...

54:35.640 --> 54:39.110
# In childhood I would roam

54:40.480 --> 54:45.554
# No-one's left to cheer me now
within that good old home... #

54:45.680 --> 54:48.513
- No. No, no! No.
- PEOPLE: Shh, shh, shh!

54:48.640 --> 54:52.713
You cannot! This is her song!
That is her song! Stop this! Stop!

54:52.840 --> 54:55.878
- # ...Sister and brother now lay... #
- Stop this! This is her song!

54:56.000 --> 54:58.310
- # ...Beneath the clay... #
- Mr Reid! Come.

54:58.440 --> 55:00.670
- # ...But while life does remain... #
- You cannot. You cannot.

55:00.800 --> 55:03.030
It cannot be allowed!
Stop this, damn it! Stop!

55:03.160 --> 55:04.992
- (AUDIENCE SINGS ALONG)
- Quiet, sir!

55:05.120 --> 55:09.034
# ...This small violet I plucked
from Mother's grave... #

55:09.160 --> 55:11.037
Do you not know any respect?

55:12.120 --> 55:14.714
Or is that you do not know at all?
It is her song!

55:14.840 --> 55:17.070
It is the song that
Mary Jane Kelly was heard to sing

55:17.200 --> 55:18.873
the night the Ripper killed her!

55:19.000 --> 55:20.229
Mr Reid.

55:20.360 --> 55:23.512
Is that not the reason
why it is sung?

55:23.640 --> 55:26.075
# ...This flower has brought me joy

55:26.200 --> 55:28.476
# So while life does remain... #

55:28.600 --> 55:32.798
Please, sir.
Perhaps it is time you went home.

55:32.920 --> 55:35.992
# ...This small violet
I plucked from Mother's grave... #

55:36.120 --> 55:38.475
Yes, of course.

55:38.600 --> 55:40.352
I'm, erm...

55:40.480 --> 55:42.551
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

55:44.720 --> 55:46.836
I'm sorry.

57:01.760 --> 57:04.479
(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

57:59.440 --> 58:00.350
(FRAME CLICKS SHUT)

58:00.480 --> 58:02.357
(DRAWER CLOSES)

58:37.080 --> 58:38.957
(CLOCKS CHIME)

58:39.080 --> 58:40.957
(CHEERING)

